Hey y’all! So l I’ve developed a new skill and have been intrigued with tending to plants for the past year… It’s actually been quite therapeutic for me, and being that I naturally like to care for things, I’m officially becoming a green thumb! Lol I thought it would be cool if I shared my journey with you all, because I’m still new to this and this could possibly spark someone else’s interest in owning a plant. If you have any tips/tricks that you would like to share with me along the way, please feel free to comment them below! 

Common causes of Peace lily drooping leaves:
* under-watering/over-watering 
* being pot bound (outgrowing it’s pot) 
* too much light/temperature shock 

In this case, my peace lily was bound to its nursery pot and it was time for it to be repotted… 

Tips to find the perfect pot for your plant:
* make sure it has a large enough drainage hole/holes to avoid your plant sitting in water and developing root rot
* choose a pot that’s only 1”-2” larger than the last pot
* remember repotting your plant overtime & upgrading to a slightly larger pot will promote your plant to grow bigger!

🤍✨ there’s self-care… which makes us feel so good on the outside… but then there’s “self-love”… which is an inside job that’s not always pretty, but it brings about life changing results that will propel you forward… Whatever self-love looks like to you, whether it’s setting healthy boundaries with others or even yourself, overcoming that trauma, journaling to yourself, reading a book, listening to an empowering/educational podcast everyday, whatever is bettering your physical/mental/spiritual health… KEEP. GOING! Remain consistent and don’t allow anyone or anything to knock you off your pivot! Do the inner work… it may require a lot of discipline and finding a balance, but your future self will thank you! Try not to become distracted with the physical, surface-level things in life… they won’t bring you happiness overall. Everything you desire to change or obtain starts with YOU. I don’t know who needed to hear this, but I hope this message gave you a boost! This is me holding myself accountable and I hope this did the same for you! Shout out to @ceomrsmatty for dropping so many beautiful gems yesterday at her event 💓 it definitely confirmed that I’m on the right path and taking the necessary steps to show up as the woman God envisioned me to be! I plan to be a little more personable on here because who knows how sharing my journey can impact someone else in a positive light. I encourage everyone to try using their platform for moments of transparency and sharing pieces of their journey, because even by that, you’re practicing “self-love”

Love, 
Meilani

Chill fit vs “Put together” Chill fit 

You notice how I’m dressed down in sweats for both outfits but one looks more feminine & put together? Key difference is:
• Color of clothing - soft, colorful clothes look more inviting 
• No jewelry vs jewelry - jewelry adds femininity to your attire 
• No makeup vs makeup - A little touch of makeup can enhance the features that you already have. (Beware of wearing too much, which could hide and distract people from your natural beauty)
• Hair is styled and looks healthy 

To be completely honest, majority of the time I’m rocking the “chill fit” with no makeup. However, I’m going to work towards putting more effort into my routine so I’m always looking “put together”. There isn’t anything wrong with the “chill, no makeup look”, but I think we all can admit that the more “put together look” comes off as ‘you woke up on time this morning’, or you’ll be ready for an opportunity if it were to present itself at random. First impressions are everything 💗  In my opinion, simple little touches to your routine can boost your confidence, help you appear more reliable and trustworthy (especially if you’re a professional), and it may help you attract more. And for my non-makeup wearing ladies: You don’t HAVE to wear makeup. But when your skin is clear, healthy, and hydrated, and you’re rocking some mascara, lashes or mink extensions, that also looks well put together & attractive! 

What are your thoughts?
